title: For Sale:  LWRC M6-IC-SPR 5.56 DARK EARTH New
postcontent: The new M6 Individual Carbine family is the direct descendant of the rifles developed by LWRCI™ to meet the requirements of the U.S. Army Individual Carbine program. It includes some revolutionary new features while maintaining the basic M4/AR15/M16 architecture that has served our nation’s armed forces well for the past 40 years. All members of the IC family feature our new fully ambidextrous lower receiver. Dual controls for bolt catch and release, magazine release, and fire control mean that both right- and left- handed shooters can use the rifle to its full effectiveness. In addition, dual controls give shooters the option of using their offhand side to accommodate barriers or injury. They can effectively manipulate the controls without having to switch hands. Despite its dramatically improved functionality, this new dual control lower receiver is compatible with all legacy AR15 pattern upper receivers. The Monoforge™ upper receiver used in all members of the IC family is a further evolution of the M6A2-SPR platform introduced by LWRCI™ in 2011. It features a user-configurable rail system. title: For Sale:  AR-15 80% Lower & Jig
postcontent:
Here is what you need to start building your very own, original AR-15 Lower Receiver.  
With only 80% of the milling done, the BATF considers the 80% Lower to be nothing more than an Aluminum Paperweight, so NO FFL is needed.  I will ship it straight to you.
This 80% can be finished out with a Drill Press or a Mini Mill.  If you don't own one of these, check around, Build Parties are a popular way to gain access to the machinery needed to finish out the build.  
There are many tutorials out there:

https://colfaxtactical.com/instructions.html
http://www.calguns.net/calgunforum/showthread.php?t=271990
http://vadertactical.com/

Randy Spade over at vadertactical.com does some amazing work, and has what I consider the best DIY instructions out there.  

I also have the listed locally, so the first $250 gets it.
Have a Blessed 2014!!!

title: For Sale:  WWI Colt 1911
postcontent:
I have a hard to find WWI Colt 1911 .45 ACP, serial number 347XXX. It was built in 1918 and appears to have seen all of the conflicts the U.S. has been involved in, through Vietnam. It has been re-blued, but retains strong roll marks. As far as I can tell, it has all original parts except mainspring housing, grips and barrel (which appears to be a post-WWII Springfield replacement). A replacement trigger is pictured, but it will be sold with the original trigger. It comes with a Vietnam era M1916 style holster and a WWI American Pin "A" magazine. 

This pistol will make a great shooter for anyone who wants to show off an old WW war horse. I have fired the weapon with no issues. For a 96 year old gun it works beautifully. I was able to consistently hit cans from 20 yards. Again, this gun is a great piece of shootable history!

title: For Sale:  Original Henry Rifle” Tribute to B. Tyler Henry        2014 SHOT Show
postcontent:
The Henry rifle became known as the rifle you could "Load on Sunday and shoot all week long." After the war, the Henry rifle headed west and went on to play a significant role in the homesteading of that great frontier.

Now, the Original Henry Rifle is back in all its American-made glory. This Original Henry Rifle is virtually identical to its history-making forerunner in all aspects, except caliber. This modern rifle is .44-40 caliber. The 1860 version was .44 Rimfire. The .44 Rimfire was also invented by B. Tyler Henry, but is now an obsolete cartridge. Every other facet of this new Original Henry remains true to its inventor and, in his honor, each gun's serial number in the new production will begin with the initials BTH. The only exception will be this SHOT Show Henry Tribute rifle, which will feature serial number BTHENRY001.
